		<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
		<tr>
		    <td valign="top">
		     <p><font face="Verdana" size="3"><b>Article Title:</b>&nbsp;</font>
		     <font face="Verdana" size="2">No Trivial Loot Code For Luclin</font><br>
		     <a href = "../Subscribe.asp?DID=496457" ><font face="Verdana" size="2">[Subscribe to this document]</font></a></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
		
		<tr><td>&nbsp;</tr><tr>
		
		    <td valign="top">
		    <p><font face="Verdana" size="2">
		    Brad posted the following <a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/ubb/everquest/Forum1/HTML/000320.html"  >announcement</a> regarding the trivial loot code for luclin:
<blockquote>
<p>
Hello all,</p>
<p>
I wanted to update you all on our current thoughts regarding the Trivial Loot Code as it relates to Shadows of Luclin zones.</p>
<p>
As per my last couple of 'Ask Brads', we've made both an effort to explain what the Trivial Loot Code does and why we were considering it for all Luclin zones. I'd also mentioned, however, that if most players appeared to be against its inclusion we'd not use it.</p>
<p>
After talking with players, reading emails and feedback, and then very recently running a poll, it is indeed apparent that the majority of our playerbase does not feel that the Loot Code's advantages outweigh its restrictions.</p>
<p>
In fact, after polling over 200,000 players, most want the looting system left alone, almost as many want us to explore a different solution for bottom feeding and rampant farming, and a minority were in favor of the Trivial Loot Code as it exists today in the Warrens and Stonebrunt Mountains (the remainder either didn't have an opinion or were unfamiliar with TLC).</p>
<p>
Well, so be it</p>
<p>
We will head back to our drawing boards and keep brainstorming on this issue, but at this current time we do NOT intend on implementing TLC for the zones in our upcoming expansion, the Shadows of Luclin.</p>
<p>
I do want to thank everyone for all the feedback and discussion regarding this issue -- there was a lot of debate surrounding this issue, and we've done our best to pay attention.</p>
<p>
-Brad McQuaid<br>
Chief Creative Officer & Vice President<br>
Sony Online Entertainment/Verant Interactive</p>
</blockquote>
		    </font></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
